
1) Create the following code snippets:
    - Completion: mark
      Snippet: // MARK: - <#SECTION#>

    - Completion: disableconstrainterrors
      Snippet: UserDefaults.standard.setValue(false, forKey: "_UIConstraintBasedLayoutLogUnsatisfiable")
      Explanation: Add this to onAppear in the App file to fix the errors resulting from NavigationViews in SwiftUI. See https://stackoverflow.com/questions/65316497/swiftui-navigationview-navigationbartitle-layoutconstraints-issue

    - Completion: .tm
      Snippet: modifier(TextMod(<#FONT#>, <#WEIGHT#>))
      Explanation: Must have XAV_Customs package or at least TextMod modifier.

    - Completion: .preview
      Snippet:
      struct <#STRUCT_NAME#>_Previews: PreviewProvider {
            static var previews: some View {
                <#STRUCT_NAME#>()
            }
        }


2) Helpful Packages
    - https://github.com/siteline/SwiftUI-Introspect
      Introspect allows you to get the underlying UIKit or AppKit element of a SwiftUI view.
